criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  response to an advertisement for the study;

          -  has only one child aged 4-5 years old in the family;

          -  speaks English;

          -  family with income within 185% of the Federal Poverty Guideline Levels determined by
             parents' self-report;

          -  has a TV with HDMI port or VGA port or video port at home

          -  the child has no medical conditions or physical disabilities that prohibit engagement
             in PA;

          -  physically inactive child who does not meet 120 min. PA per day;

          -  parental agreement to participating in the home visits and evaluations;

          -  lives within 20 miles of the UMN;

          -  family willingness to commit to 6 months of intervention and 6 months of follow-up;

          -  not moving out of area for the next 12 months.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  children/parents from families that already own exergame(s) as these children tend to
             possess high experience levels with exergaming play;

          -  child who are physically active for more than recommended 180 min. PA per day as
             reported by parents.
